  "body": "I have created a new account, backed up address and passphrase, mined for a few months and now when I want to spend my eth I can't access it.\r\n\r\nWhy? Because I had no idea I there is something called keystore and I need to back it up.\r\n\r\nAnd this hasn't improved at all. Geth is still actively losing users money!\r\nLook at the output of newest geth I could install: 1.8.23-stable-c9427004\r\n\r\n```\r\ngeth account new\r\nINFO [02-25|13:19:00.805] Maximum peer count                       ETH=25 LES=0 total=25\r\nYour new account is locked with a password. Please give a password. Do not forget this password.\r\nPassphrase: \r\nRepeat passphrase: \r\nAddress: {70f795db0a6198163df9c42192a8673ad705e929}\r\n```\r\nIt mentions the passphrase and the address. There are no messages about keystore.\r\n\r\nThat's because keystore is not important at all and can be recreated if you know the address and the passphrase, right? Right?\r\n\r\nWrong! When it's time to spend your money it's headache time when you understand you lost your eth. Because you really need the keystore which isn't mentioned anywhere.\r\n\r\nHow about adding this to the message?\r\n\r\n```\r\nTo backup this wallet you need to backup:\r\n* X\r\n* Y \r\n* Z\r\n\r\nTo read more about backing up and restoring your account please visit:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/whatever.\r\n\r\n```\r\n",
